{
  "texts": [
    "Corresponding to different representation forms of the user interest, there are also various storage forms in the interest memory.• Historical item lists refer to representing personalized users based on the sequence of historical interacted items, which is widely used in session-based recommendation and sequential recommendation [43,51,188].",
    "For token-based item indexing, the ID sequence of items is used for user modeling in LLMs, similar to traditional sequential recommendation models [32].",
    "However, without fine-tuning, LLMs cannot recognize the meaning of corresponding IDs.",
    "For descriptionbased item indexing, existing researches generally concatenate the attributes (e.g., titles) of items in the temporal order, and then input the item sequence as text descriptions to LLMs as user representations [44,59,72].",
    "Only the item IDs that the user has interacted with need to be stored as the interest memory."
  ]
}